3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network calculates AAVE/USDT funding rates every hour based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices across its shared order book. The rate is distributed across multiple DEX frontends including WOOFi Pro and Ref Finance, creating unified funding mechanics. Traders pay or receive funding based on their position direction and the 8-hour time-weighted average premium, with settlements occurring automatically through Orderly's infrastructure layer."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","AAVE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE's role as a leading DeFi lending protocol creates natural funding rate volatility during governance events and protocol updates. The token's correlation with broader DeFi sentiment often generates sustained funding rate imbalances, particularly during yield farming cycles and lending market stress periods."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE/USDT on Orderly Network has exhibited funding rate ranges of -0.15% to +0.25% during high volatility periods, with DeFi governance events creating the most significant rate spikes. Summer 2024 saw consistent positive rates averaging 0.08% as institutional interest in DeFi lending protocols increased. The shared liquidity model tends to moderate extreme rates compared to isolated DEX perpetual markets. Rate volatility typically correlates with Ethereum gas fee fluctuations and broader DeFi TVL movements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-DEX Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly's multi-frontend architecture enables arbitrage between different DEX interfaces accessing the same underlying liquidity. Rate discrepancies of 0.02-0.05% frequently occur between WOOFi Pro and Ref Finance due to varying user bases and trading patterns. The NEAR/EVM bridge integration creates additional arbitrage potential when Ethereum-based AAVE perpetuals diverge from Orderly rates. Traders can exploit these inefficiencies while benefiting from the shared order book's improved liquidity depth."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network's reliance on frontend partners introduces counterparty risk beyond typical DEX exposure, as interface availability affects position management capabilities. The complex architecture spanning NEAR and EVM chains creates potential bridge risks during periods of network congestion. AAVE's governance token status means funding positions can be severely impacted by unexpected protocol votes or security incidents. Lower trading volumes compared to major CEX platforms may result in wider spreads during volatile periods, affecting arbitrage profitability."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often do AAVE funding rates update on Orderly Network?","answer":"Orderly Network updates AAVE/USDT funding rates every hour based on the perpetual-spot premium calculation. The 8-hour time-weighted average determines actual funding payments, providing more frequent rate adjustments than traditional DEX perpetual platforms."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage AAVE funding rates across different Orderly frontends?","answer":"No, all Orderly Network frontends share the same underlying order book and funding rates. However, you can arbitrage between Orderly and other DEX/CEX platforms that offer AAVE perpetuals with different rate structures."},{"question":"What makes AAVE funding rates unique on decentralized exchanges?","answer":"AAVE funding rates on DEX platforms like Orderly often show higher volatility due to lower trading volumes and the token's correlation with DeFi governance events. The decentralized nature also means rates may not converge as quickly with centralized exchange rates during market stress."},{"question":"How do Orderly Network's fees affect AAVE funding arbitrage profitability?","answer":"Orderly charges 0.02% maker and 0.05% taker fees, which must be factored into arbitrage calculations alongside funding rates. The shared liquidity model often provides better execution than isolated DEX markets, potentially offsetting the fee impact for larger position sizes."}]}]
